    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Racial Bridges, Open and Closed</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fred Polvere letter says series about racial relations in America clearly points out how far apart blacks and whites are in their attitudes</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your excellent series ''How Race Is Lived in America'' clearly points out how far we are from bridging the gap in race relations in this country.</p>
        <p>Most revealing is the attitudinal difference between whites who find that ''blacks are too concerned with race and bring it into everything'' and blacks who counter that with ''you can't understand because you are not black.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your excellent series ''How Race Is Lived in America'' clearly points out how far we are from bridging the gap in race relations in this country.</p>
        <p>Most revealing is the attitudinal difference between whites who find that ''blacks are too concerned with race and bring it into everything'' and blacks who counter that with ''you can't understand because you are not black.''</p>
        <p>The saddest part of this divide is that both sides are right.</p>
        <p>FRED POLVERE  Yonkers, June 15, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
